  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nAt some point I saw my node kept processing through checkpoints. The debug shown that it has to do `processSlotsToNearestCheckpoint` from slot 503119 to 572736, almost 70000 slots!\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2020-10-23 at 09 57 38](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/96951403-9f3d7180-1516-11eb-90b1-5fbf44c3edda.png)\r\n\r\nNote this log: `Checkpoint processed epoch=15725, root=0x3b931133a8897f0785da2754e57c1e535a77e3388aaccaac26496cc882c56e8e` happened a lot. Root is the same, epoch is increased gradually\r\n\r\nThe result is the node is very busy processing that request.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n+ Figure out what caused the issue and prevent it\r\n+ This is the log file\r\n[processSlotsToNearestCheckpoint.log.zip](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/files/5427059/processSlotsToNearestCheckpoint.log.zip)\r\n\r\n",
